================================================================================
Modifications from the upstream template
================================================================================

The following modifications were made when deriving this template from the
upstream commit listed above. They are summarised here per Section 4 of the
Apache License, Version 2.0, which requires that modifications carry
prominent notices stating that changes have been made.

1. Copier render
   The upstream repository is a Copier template (https://copier.readthedocs.io)
   that requires the `nava-platform` CLI to render. The derivation rendered
   the template once with a sentinel `app_name` placeholder and committed the
   rendered output at the repository root, so that consumers can use the
   template directly without installing copier or the nava-platform CLI.

2. nava-platform machinery removal
   The following nava-platform-specific files and directories were removed
   from the upstream copy after rendering:
     - copier.yml, code.json, .copier-answers.yml
     - template/, template-only-bin/, template-only-docs/
     - renovate.json (Nava-Renovate-specific config)
     - CODEOWNERS (Nava-team-specific)
     - SECURITY.md (replaced with a DSO-maintained version)
     - CONTRIBUTING.md (replaced; DSO contribution flow lives in the DSO
       plugin repo)
     - .github/workflows/template-only-*.yml
     - rendered nava-style CI workflows (replaced with a DSO ci.yml)

3. {{PROJECT_NAME}} placeholders
   String literals identifying the project (package.json `name`, README
   title, in-repo path references) were replaced with the literal token
   `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`. The `create-dso-app` installer in the
   `digital-service-orchestra` plugin substitutes this token with the
   user's sanitized project name at scaffold time.

4. DSO infrastructure
   The following pre-populated files were added to support the Digital
   Service Orchestra (DSO) Claude Code plugin workflow:
     - CLAUDE.md (Claude Code project configuration)
     - project-understanding.md, design-notes.md
     - .claude/ARCH_ENFORCEMENT.md, .claude/dso-config.conf
     - .pre-commit-config.yaml (eslint/prettier/typecheck + DSO hook stubs)
     - .github/workflows/ci.yml (DSO-tagged CI pipeline)
     - SECURITY.md (DSO security contact)

5. Tickets orphan branch
   A `tickets` orphan branch with an empty initial commit was added so the
   DSO ticket-tracker subsystem can populate it on first use inside a
   scaffolded project.

